-- Brazil Creates Stimulus Package for Ethanol Industry, Valor Says
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2012-05-31T13:49:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-31/brazil-creates-stimulus-package-for-ethanol-industry-valor-says.html
Brazil  is developing a fiscal
stimulus package for the nation’s ethanol industry to boost its
competitiveness,  Valor Economico  reported, citing a government
official it didn’t identify.  The package may include tax breaks on investments made in
new plants and on ethanol production, the Sao Paulo-based
newspaper said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at 
 snielsen8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  